{"add":{"doc":{"id":"54631b957a9e934364169c35ed5f6727d6604e9b0712d94b177dad7362494a9d","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/All_People%27s_Congress_political_rally_Sierra_Leone_1968.jpg/300px-All_People%27s_Congress_political_rally_Sierra_Leone_1968.jpg","previous":[],"after":["Stevens assumed power again in 1968 with a great deal of hope and ambition. Much trust was placed upon him as he championed multi-party politics. Stevens had campaigned on a platform of bringing the tribes together under socialist principles. During his first decade or so in power, Stevens renegotiated some of what he called \"useless prefinanced schemes\" contracted by his predecessors, both Albert Margai of the SLPP and Juxon-Smith of the NRC. Some of these policies by the SLPP and the NRC were said to have left the country in an economically deprived state."]}}}